cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.MS, cs.CE 

The paper discusses issues related to software development and maintenance for scientific computing, which is a broad area that can be categorized under several sub-categories. The focus on licensing, code sharing, and code maintenance suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The discussion of parallelism and memory hierarchies suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The mention of open access publishing suggests cs.MS (Mathematical Software), and the discussion of education and training suggests cs.CE (Computers and Education).
